      "questionText": "A similarity between optical and geometrical isomerism is that",
      "options": [
        "each forms equal number of isomers for a given compound",
        "if in a compound one is present then so is the other",
        "both are included in stereoisomerism",
        "they have no similarity"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "isomerism",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Stereoisomerism involve those isomers which contain same ligands in their co-ordination spheres but differ in the arrangement of those ligands in space. Stereo-isomerism is of two type geometrical isomerism ligands occupy different positions around the central metal atom or  ion. \n<br><br><b>NOTE :</b> In optical isomerism isomers have same formula but differ in their ability to rotate directions of the plane of polarized light. ",
