      "id": "1l5bddpj1",
      "questionNumber": 10,
      "questionText": "<p>Arrange the following carbocations in decreasing order of stability.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l5cm70wm/ad569d3c-b895-4815-8172-1701ae45228f/e6d9bf60-fed2-11ec-8624-ff35f7fd77e0/file-1l5cm70wn.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l5cm70wm/ad569d3c-b895-4815-8172-1701ae45228f/e6d9bf60-fed2-11ec-8624-ff35f7fd77e0/file-1l5cm70wn.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 24th June Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 160 English\"></p>",
      "options": [
        "B > A > C",
        "A > B > C",
        "C > B > A",
        "C > A > B"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "stability-of-intermediate",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "The given carbocations are<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8medbsd/343005fd-b7c6-4b2c-97ce-9fcdf6d7c292/c9b589d0-3f98-11ed-be5e-93aeba6c60fe/file-1l8medbse.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8medbsd/343005fd-b7c6-4b2c-97ce-9fcdf6d7c292/c9b589d0-3f98-11ed-be5e-93aeba6c60fe/file-1l8medbse.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 24th June Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 160 English Explanation 1\"><br>\nCarbocation (A) is stabilised by hyperconjugation due to $4 \\alpha$ hydrogen atoms. Carbocation (C) is also stabilised by hyperconjugation due to 4 a hydrogen atoms but destabilised by $-1$ effect of O-atom. Carbocation (B) is most stable as it is stabilised by resonance.\n<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8mefeo9/ceeed3b8-bbc8-45ac-9c08-1ede249ddc2a/038e7f90-3f99-11ed-be5e-93aeba6c60fe/file-1l8mefeoa.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8mefeo9/ceeed3b8-bbc8-45ac-9c08-1ede249ddc2a/038e7f90-3f99-11ed-be5e-93aeba6c60fe/file-1l8mefeoa.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 45vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2022 (Online) 24th June Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 160 English Explanation 2\"><br>\n$\\therefore$ Correct decreasing order of stability is $$\n\\text { B }&gt;\\text { A }&gt;\\text { C }\n$$",
